# Proyecto-Estimacion-Soft — Cursor Rules
# Stack: React 18 + TypeScript | Node.js + Express | MongoDB | Docker
# Authors: Adrian Alexander Alvarez Gonzalez & Ray Rubén Ventura López (UCE)

## Skills Available
All skills are located in `.antigravity/skills/`. Before implementing any feature,
read the relevant SKILL.md file first. Key skills:

- Planning & Architecture: @.antigravity/skills/planning-with-files/SKILL.md
- React/TypeScript tests: @.antigravity/skills/javascript-typescript-jest/SKILL.md
- Web forms: @.antigravity/skills/create-web-form/SKILL.md
- Commits: @.antigravity/skills/conventional-commit/SKILL.md
- Backend refactor: @.antigravity/skills/review-and-refactor/SKILL.md
- Docker: @.antigravity/skills/multi-stage-dockerfile/SKILL.md

## Code Standards
- Language: TypeScript strict mode everywhere
- Frontend: React 18 functional components only, no class components
- Styling: Tailwind CSS only — use existing delphi-* color tokens
- Backend: Express + Mongoose, async/await pattern, no callbacks
- Auth: JWT via httpOnly cookies only — never expose tokens in response body
- Commits: MUST follow conventional commit format (feat/fix/chore/docs/test/refactor)
- No TODO comments — implement fully or open a GitHub issue

## Branch Strategy
- main: production only
- develop: integration branch — all PRs target here
- feature/*: one feature per branch, named after RF/RNF number
- Adrian owns: feature/RF001-RF005-auth-security, feature/RNF005-docker-ci
- Ray owns: feature/RF006-RF034-domain-engine, feature/RF015-RF022-statistics-convergence

## File Ownership — DO NOT MODIFY without coordination
- Ray's files: server/src/models/Project.model.ts, Round.model.ts, Estimation.model.ts
- Adrian's files: server/src/controllers/auth.controller.ts, admin.controller.ts,
  server/src/middleware/auth.middleware.ts, server/src/middleware/rbac.middleware.ts,
  components/Login.tsx, components/AdminPanel.tsx, services/authService.ts

## Planning Protocol
For every new feature:
1. Read @.antigravity/skills/planning-with-files/SKILL.md
2. Create PLANNING.md in root with the feature plan
3. Get approval before writing any implementation code
4. Update PLANNING.md checkboxes as you complete each step
5. Delete PLANNING.md after final commit and PR creation
